-- CTGuard (closed): a `match` with guarded ARMS (`pat if guard => body`) lowers
-- to a decision tree carrying `CTGuard` nodes — distinct from function-level
-- guard arms, which desugar to if-chains.  Each guard tests a Bool and falls
-- through to the next clause on failure (here a var pattern + guard chain).
-- sign 5 = 1 ; sign 0 = 0 ; sign (-3) = -1
-- main = 1 + 0*10 + (-1)*100 = -99
sign n = match n
  m if m > 0 => 1
  m if m == 0 => 0
  _ => 0 - 1

main = sign 5 + sign 0 * 10 + sign (0 - 3) * 100
